title: Italian Gothic Sculpture (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
pdf / English / 1955 Phaidon / 228 pag / 56.1 MB

This volume covers a period bounded at one end by the pulpits of Nicola Pisano and at the other bv the bronze doors of Ghiberti. It comprises a general introduction, in which the stylistic development of Italian Gothic sculpture is presented as a continuous whole, 108 plates offering a representative cross-section of each sculptor's work, more than a hundred illustrations in the text, biographies of the artists whose work is discussed, and detailed notes on the works illustrated
